text.tspan: Switzerland: COVID-19 weekly death rate by vaccination status, All
Death rates are calculated as the number of deaths in each group, divided by the total number of people in this group. This is given
Data source: Federal Office of Public Health
Note: Data coverage includes both Switzerland and Liechtenstein. Unvaccinated people have not received any dose. Partially-vaccinated people are
excluded. Fully-vaccinated people have received all doses prescribed by the initial vaccination protocol. The mortality rate for the 'All ages' group is
age-standardized to account for the different vaccination rates of older and younger people.
